	doi = {10.29115/SP-2024-0006},
	abstract = {Sun and Yan (2023) described a Computer-Assisted Recorded Interviewing (CARI) Machine Learning (ML) pipeline that efficiently processes 100\% of recorded interviews as quickly as possible and as inexpensively as possible. The CARI ML pipeline leads to automatic identification of recordings that are at a higher risk of being falsified or exhibiting undesirable interviewer behaviors. This paper describes an extension to the pipeline that can be used to automatically detect survey questions at a higher risk of poor performance. A proof-of-concept study was conducted and showed that the enhanced pipeline was able to detect worst performing items judged by experts. The results demonstrated the potential of the enhanced pipeline to screen and select problematic items for conventional behavior coding and to improve the efficiency of using CARI for question evaluation and testing.},
